When twilight falls and shadows blend,  
And day gives way to night,  
I see the world in peace descend,  
In stars, a quiet light.  

The whispers of the earth resound,  
In voices soft and low;  
Each momentâ€™s grace is tightly wound,  
In nature's gentle flow.

- John Muir
